claim.claim-text:
1. An electronic assistant, comprising: 
a non-electronic personal object with an electronic module incorporated therein, said personal object having utility beyond that of the electronic module incorporated therein; 
said at least one electronic module includes at least one of a PDA, a cell phone, a navigation module generating navigation data, a biosensor module generating physical user state data, and an emergency alert module generating a local and/or remote alarm signal.

10. An electronic assistant, comprising: 
non-electronic personal object with an electronic module incorporated therein, said personal object having utility beyond that of the electronic module incorporated therein; 
said personal object being one of a cane, a walking stick, a walker, a wheelchair, a personal transportation vehicle, a purse, a key holder, a watch, a pendant, a hearing aid, an eyeglass frame, and a crutch; 
said at least one electronic module including at least one of a PDA, a cell phone, a navigation module, a biosensor module, and an emergency alert module; 
said navigation module including at least one of a GPS, an altimeter, an electronic compass, and a stored map; 
said biosensor module including at least one biosensor, a biosensor information processor, and at least one biosensor communication channel connecting each said at least one biosensor with said biosensor information processor; 
each said at least one biosensor being one of a biosensor disposed in a surface of said personal object, a remote biosensor attached to the body of the user, and a remote biosensor surgically implanted in the body of said user; 
said biosensor communication channel being at least one of a wire, a radio frequency transmitter and receiver, and an infrared transmitter and receiver; and 
said emergency alert module including an emergency button, and an emergency notification sequence stored in said electronic assistant capable of calling for assistance through said cell phone.

11. A method of assisting a user, comprising the steps of: 
integrating a digital assistant into a commonly-used personal object that provides utility apart from said digital assistant; 
programming said digital assistant to receive and classify at least one biosignal to generate a user state signal; 
receiving at least one biosensor signal with said digital assistant; 
generating an output with said digital assistant responsively to said biosensor signal.
